    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Describes a type of dance characterized by elaborately decorated regalia, including feathered bustles and roaches, and fast-paced movements. Commonly performed at powwows by Native North American men. Popularized at powwow events in the 1960s, though  has origins in 19th century Plains dances.</Note_Text>
